        q: `A 20-year-old healthy man is bitten by a rattlesnake during a camping trip. His friends rapidly transport him to a hospital where he is given an injection of anti-venom serum produced by immunizing horses with rattlesnake venom. Twelve days later he develops diffuse joint pains and passes red blood cells in urine. Blood tests are most likely to reveal which of the following immunologic alterations?`,
