        optionFeedback: [`Anti-dsDNA antibodies are specific for SLE.`,`Anti-centromere antibodies are found in limited forms of scleroderma.`,`Dryness of the mouth and eyes caused by inflammatory involvement of salivary and lacrimal glands is the characteristic feature of Sj&#246;gren syndrome. Antibodies against the nuclear antigens SS-A and SS-B (Sj&#246;gren syndrome-related antigens A and B) are found in many autoimmune diseases, including systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), but are most prevalent in Sj&#246;gren syndrome. By themselves, they are not diagnostic of any autoimmune disease.`,`Anti-topoisomerase antibodies are found in systemic sclerosis.`,`Antibodies reactive with nucleolar antigens are seen in many autoimmune diseases. They are more often seen in systemic sclerosis.`],
