        ansText: `Rationale:-Dryness of the mouth and eyes caused by inflammatory involvement of salivary and lacrimal glands is the characteristic feature of Sj&#246;gren syndrome. Antibodies against the nuclear antigens SS-A and SS-B (Sj&#246;gren syndrome-related antigens A and B) are found in many autoimmune diseases, including systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), but are most prevalent in Sj&#246;gren syndrome. By themselves, they are not diagnostic of any autoimmune disease. `,
