        ansText: `Rationale:- The clinical features should raise the suspicion of systemic lupus erythematosus with lupus nephritis, which would account for the abnormal renal function tests, proteinuria (causing peripheral edema), and microscopic hematuria. The renal histology is classic for diffuse proliferative glomerulonephritis, (Chapter 11) the most common and severe form of lupus nephritis. The most specific antibody in this disease is anti–double stranded DNA antibody. `,
