        q: `A 22-year-old woman has a 1-week history of increasing malaise and swelling of her feet. On physical examination, she has 2+ pitting edema to the knees and puffiness around the eyes. Laboratory studies show serum creatinine of 4.6 mg/dL (0.6–1.2 mg/dL) and urea nitrogen of 42 mg/dL (7–18 mg/dL). A renal biopsy shows granular immunofluorescent staining for immunoglobulin and complement C3 within the glomeruli. Which of the following additional clinical features is most likely to be present in this patient?`,
