        optionFeedback: [`Dysphagia is often seen in systemic sclerosis because of fibrosis of the esophageal wall.`,`Asthma is an allergic disease not related to SLE.`,`This patient has renal disease with features of the nephrotic syndrome (proteinuria, peripheral edema). The immunofluorescence is diagnostic for an immune complex disease. In a young woman, the likely diagnosis is systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE). Individuals with SLE develop not only immune complex lesions but also make autoantibodies against blood cells, resulting in variable cytopenias.`,`Keratoconjunctivitis due to inflammatory destruction of lacrimal glands is typical of Sj&#246;gren syndrome.`,`Atherosclerotic aortic aneurysms are not related to SLE, but patients do develop lesions of cardiac valves (Libman-Sacks endocarditis) and have a propensity to develop coronary artery disease.`],
