        optionFeedback: [`Type I interferon is typically produced in systemic lupus erythematosus and is not a cause of fibrosis. `,`This patient has evidence of fibrosis in the esophagus (causing dysphagia) and lungs (resulting in dyspnea), and narrowing of small blood vessels (causing Raynaud phenomenon) along with antibodies to DNA topoisomerase—all characteristic of systemic sclerosis. TGF-β is a potent activator of fibroblasts, which lay down collagen and may contribute to the widespread fibrosis in this disease.`,`IL-17 has multiple actions that do not include fibrosis.`,`IL-2 is a growth factor for T cells, but does not induce fibrosis.`,`IL-4 has multiple actions that do not include fibrosis.`],
        optionStyleType: `st-upper-alpha`,
