        ansText: `Rationale:-This patient has evidence of fibrosis in the esophagus (causing dysphagia) and lungs (resulting in dyspnea), and narrowing of small blood vessels (causing Raynaud phenomenon) along with antibodies to DNA topoisomerase—all characteristic of systemic sclerosis. TGF-β is a potent activator of fibroblasts, which lay down collagen and may contribute to the widespread fibrosis in this disease.  `,
