        optionFeedback: [`<i>Pneumocystis</i> infection with reduced CD4+ T cell counts is strongly suggestive of HIV infection. This patient would have anti-HIV antibodies.`,`Anti-dsDNA antibody is seen in the autoimmune disease systemic lupus erythematosus, which is not associated with <i>Pneumocystis</i> infection or reduced CD4+ T cells.`,`HTLV-1 is a retrovirus like HIV and infects CD4+ cells. It causes human T cell leukemia/lymphoma and is not associated with AIDS.`,`Anti-streptolysin O (ASLO) is seen after streptococcal infection, and often in acute rheumatic fever.`,`There are no known diseases in which patients make antibodies to their own T cells.`],
